Package: elbe-doc
Section: doc
Architecture: all
Depends: ${misc:Depends}
Description: ELBE documentation.
 Manpages and documentation for ELBE. ELBE (embedded linux build environment)
 is a flexible Root Filesystem builder.

Package: elbe-common
Architecture: all
Depends: ${misc:Depends},
  python (>= 2.7~),
  python-lxml,
  python-apt,
  python-gpgme,
  python-pyme
Description: ELBE common files.
 Common files for ELBE (embedded linux build environment). These
 python-modules are shared by elbe packages that are normaly not installed on
 the same (virtual) machine.

Package: elbe
Architecture: all
Depends: ${misc:Depends},
  python (>= 2.7~),
  elbe-common,
  qemu-utils,
  qemu-system,
  e2tools,
  python-mako,
  p7zip-full,
  make
Recommends: qemu-kvm, elbe-doc, elbe-control
Description: embedded linux build environment
 ELBE (embedded linux build environment) is a flexible Root Filesystem builder.
 This package is used to build a virtual machine including the 'elbe-buildenv'
 package.

Package: elbe-daemon
Architecture: all
Depends: ${misc:Depends},
  python (>= 2.7~),
  elbe-common,
  python-cherrypy3,
Description: ELBE wsgi daemon interface
 ELBE (embedded linux build environment) subcommand to start wsgi services.

Package: elbe-buildenv
Architecture: all
Depends: ${misc:Depends},
  python (>= 2.7~),
  apt-rdepends,
  binfmt-support,
  debootstrap,
  dosfstools,
  dpkg-dev,
  elbe-common,
  genisoimage,
  mtd-utils,
  python-apt,
  python-mako,
  python-parted,
  python-passlib,
  python-sqlalchemy,
  qemu-user-static,
  reprepro,
  rsync,
  kpartx
Recommends: elbe-daemon, elbe-soap
Description: ELBE build environment
 ELBE (embedded linux build environment) is a flexible Root Filesystem builder.
 This package is typically installed in a virtual machine (that can be created
 with the 'elbe init' command from the 'elbe' package). Several subcommands
 need to be executed with root privileges. It is not recommended to install
 this package on a native system.

Package: elbe-bootup-check
Architecture: all
Depends: ${misc:Depends},
  python (>= 2.7~),
  elbe-common,
  python-apt
Description: ELBE bootup check
 ELBE (embedded linux build environment) bootup checker. This package is
 typically installed on a embedded system. The bootup checker shows some
 information about the installed software on the embedded device.

Package: elbe-soap
Architecture: all
Depends: python (>= 2.7~),
  python-soaplib,
  elbe-buildenv,
  elbe-daemon
Description: SOAP Interface for elbe buildenv
 Enables remote control of the elbe buildenv via SOAP.

Package: elbe-control
Architecture: all
Depends: python (>= 2.7~),
  python-suds,
  elbe-common
Description: Commandline Tool to control an elbe buildenv
 The SOAP Interface is used to control an elbe buildenv.

Package: elbe-updated
Architecture: all
Depends: ${misc:Depends},
  python (>= 2.7~),
  elbe-common,
  python-lxml (>= 2.3.2-1),
  python-tz (>= 2012c-1),
  python-pyinotify,
  python-apt,
  python-suds,
  python-soaplib
Description: ELBE update daemon
 ELBE (embedded linux build environment) update daemon. This package is
 typically installed on a embedded system. The update daemon monitors a
 directory. If an ELBE update file (generated by 'elbe gen_update' command
 from the 'elbe-buildenv' package) is placed in this directory the update
 will be applied. Downgrades are possible by the integrated SOAP interface.
